 sale of their overstock SSD VPS.</p><table><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><strong>Buffalo 3GB SSD<br>\n</strong><p></p><ul><li>3GB RAM</li><li>4 CPU cores</li><li>30GB SSD space</li><li>1TB transfer</li><li>1Gbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li><li>Buffalo, NY, USA</li><li>$7/month</li><li>$45/year</li><li><a href=\"https://secure.ftpit.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=40\">Order here</a></li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>Buffalo 2GB SSD<br>\n</strong><p></p><ul><li>2GB RAM</li><li>2 CPU cores</li><li>25GB SSD space</li><li>1TB transfer</li><li>1Gbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li><li>Buffalo, NY, USA</li><li>$5/month</li><li>$35/year</li><li><a href=\"https://secure.ftpit.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=34\">Order here</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p><em>More offers inside!</em></p><p>FtpIt is now two years old, almost on the clock. Each of their OpenVZ servers are powered by the Intel Xeon E3-1240v2 CPU, 32GB RAM and 4 x SSD Drives with LSI Hardware RAID10. They\u2019re using 120 GB Intel 520 Series SSDs for their SSD offers. IPv6 is currently not available and no ETA has been given as to when it will be available. All orders will be activated instantly as long as you pay and pass automated fraud checks. As far as I know reviews have been mostly positive. If you are currently a customer of FtpIt, please share your experiences with us!<br>\n<span id=\"more-6169\"></span></p><table><tbody><tr><td valign=\"top\"><strong>Buffalo 1GB SSD<br>\n</strong><p></p><ul><li>1GB RAM</li><li>1 CPU core</li><li>15GB SSD space</li><li>1TB transfer</li><li>1Gbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li><li>Buffalo, NY, USA</li><li>$3.5/month</li><li>$30/year</li><li><a href=\"https://secure.ftpit.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=36\">Order here</a></li></ul></td><td valign=\"top\"><strong>Los Angeles 2GB SSD<br>\n</strong><p></p><ul><li>2GB RAM</li><li>4 CPU cores</li><li>30GB SSD space</li><li>2TB transfer</li><li>1Gbps uplink</li><li>1x IPv4</li><li>OpenVZ/SolusVM</li><li>Los Angeles, CA, USA</li><li>$6/month</li><li>$48/year</li><li><a href=\"https://secure.ftpit.com/cart.php?a=add&amp;pid=105\">Order here</a></li></ul></td></tr></tbody></table><p>FtpIt currently accepts payments via PayPal, Credit and Debit Cards (via PayPal), Bitcoins (via Bitpay), and Payza. As for refunds, according to their ToS \u201cAll Payments to FtpIt are Non-Refundable\u201d. They do however offer a 99.9% uptime SLA. Additional IP addresses are $2 each per month. Spamming of any kind is strictly prohibited. For more information, take a look at their <a href=\"http://www.ftpit.com/tos.html\">Terms of Service</a> and <a href=\"http://www.ftpit.com/aup.html\">Acceptable Usage Policy</a>.</p><p><strong>Network Information</strong></p><p>Servers are located with either ColoCrossing in all locations.</p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Buffalo, NY, USA<br>\n</span>Test IPv4: 172.245.209.183<br>\nTest File: <a href=\"http://172.245.209.183/100MB.test\">http://172.245.209.183/100MB.test</a></p><p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Los Angeles, CA, USA</span><br>\nTest IPv4: 192.3.23.126<br>\nTest file: <a href=\"http://192.3.23.126/100MB.test\">http://192.3.23.126/100MB.test</a></p><p class=\"dpsp-share-text\"></p><div id=\"dpsp-content-bottom\" class=\"dpsp-content-wrapper dpsp-shape-rounded dpsp-column-auto dpsp-has-spacing dpsp-no-labels dpsp-show-on-mobile dpsp-button-style-1 dpsp-has-icon-background dpsp-has-button-background dpsp-show-total-share-count dpsp-show-total-share-count-after\"><ul class=\"dpsp-networks-btns-wrapper dpsp-networks-btns-content dpsp-has-button-icon-animation\"><li><a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=https%3A%2F%2Flowendbox.com%2Fblog%2Fftpit-openvz-ssd-vps-starting-at-3-50month-for-1gb15gb-in-buffalo%2F&amp;t=FtpIt%20-%20OpenVZ%20SSD%20VPS%20starting%20at%20%243.50%2Fmonth%20for%201GB%2F15GB%20in%20Buffalo\" class=\"dpsp-network-btn dpsp